## What is Angular?

- Framework for building client applications in HTML, CSS, JS,TS
- Clean Structure
- Reuseable code like navigation and browser histroy
- more testable 

## Prerequisite:
 - nodejs
 - node package manager : to install 3rd party lib
 - Angular cli: Autogenerated code

## Set Up Project:

- ng new hello-world(Project name)
- ng serve

## Structure of Angular Project:

-e2e: end to end test
- node modules: contain 3rd party libs that our app may depend upon
- src: src code
    - app: component
    - asset: image text file
    - environments: dev/prod
    - favicon.ico: icon
    - index.HTML
    - main.TS: starting point of applications, -> AppModule
    - polyfills.TS: import script require for angular
    - styles.CSS: global style css
    - angular-cli.json: configuration file
    - .editorconfig: editor configuration
    - karma : test runner 
    - package.json: dependencies
    - tsconfig.json: compiler configuration